commit.message:
Added YAB_WANT_GLUT compile option

This is turned off by default and should fix appveyor builds.
I could have updated appveyor config too, but we wanted to
remove glut anyway...

Fixed emulator's internal backup memory data access. This problem was happening only with saves having a specific data size. (#410)

The only game reproducing this problem is Albert Odyssey, but (I didn't looked other game in depth, so) it wouldn't be surprising to find other games reproducing the problem.

It's possible to verify this fix by using Save Data Manager application for Pseudo Saturn Kai (http://ppcenter.webou.net/pskai/pskai_release_20170423.7z -> pskai_sdm_flasher.iso) and the following steps :
 1. Backup any exiting bkram.bin file
 2. Run Yabause. In settings menu, disable BIOS usage
 3. Load pskai_sdm_flasher.iso
 4. On Save Data Manager startup, hold Z button
    (holding Z button and pressing F3 key should do the job)
 5. Press R shoulder button in order to show sub menu
 6. Select "Extra Stuff" -> "Vmem Test Bench"
 7. Exit Yabause, and restore bkram.bin if backed up in step (1)

If internal backup memory is emulated correctly, "Backup memory test passed !" is displayed on screen.
Example before fix (yabause-0.9.15-win64, 20160817) : http://ppcenter.webou.net/divers/20180117_yabause_0.9.15_original.png
After fix : http://ppcenter.webou.net/divers/20180117_yabause_0.9.15_bram_fix.png

commit.message: Updating translations for yabause/l10n/yabause_ru.yts

Detection of OpenGL failure and fallback

This change introduce the following changes:

- A new global variable "opengl disabled" used by the software renderer
  to know if it should work in "full software" or "opengl" mode;

- In the Qt port, both YabauseGL (for OpenGL) and YabauseSoftGL (for
  "full software") are now available at the same time (they used to
  be mutualy exclusive, using preprocessor black magic);

- A new YabauseGLProxy used as... yeah, you guess it: a proxy to the
  two previous objects, to avoid adding too much logic in Yabause UI;

- When Qt port fails to init Yabause, it sets the "opengl disabled"
  global variable, tells YabauseGLProxy to switch to software rendering
  again then tries to init again.

The result is you can now use "full software" mode without recompiling.

Turning off dynarec by default

It won't compile on most modern Linux distributions because
of the pointer to hardcoded memory area.

Support for different Android platforms (#351)

This change make it possible to select an Android Platform
in the different android cmake files.

It changes the platform used to compile the Yabause library
and set APP_PLATFORM to the same value for ndk-build.

Platform is set to android-19 for armeabi, making it possible
to run Yabause on really old platforms, like android-8.

Rewrote thread sleep/wake for Linux (#348)

Now using pthread condition variables instead of pause/signal.
This makes it possible to use threads in the Android port.
